        "content": {
          "ToolUseResults": {
            "tool_use_results": [
              {
                "tool_use_id": "tooluse_NltvHyIoTwC8B4yioERIBQ",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "Text": "=== Operation 1 Result (Text) ===\n# Codebase Rules and Conventions\n\n## Gem Structure\n\n### Cross-Gem Dependencies\n\n**Do not use `require_relative` across gem boundaries.**\n\nWhen one gem needs to load code from another gem, use `require` instead of `require_relative`.\n\n```ruby\n# ❌ Wrong - relative require across gems\nrequire_relative '../../../mqtt-core/lib/mqtt/core/packet/publish'\n\n# ✅ Correct - use require to respect gem boundaries\nrequire 'mqtt/core/packet/publish'\n```\n\n## Testing\n\n### Test Execution\n\n**Run individual spec files rather than the entire test suite during development.**\n\nThis avoids long-running test processes and makes debugging faster.\n\n```bash\n# ✅ Run a single spec file\nbundle exec ruby spec/client_spec.rb\n\n# ✅ Run a single test by name pattern\nbundle exec ruby spec/client_spec.rb -n '/sends qos0 publish/'\n\n# ✅ Capture long-running test output to file\nbundle exec ruby spec/client_spec.rb > test_results.txt 2>&1\n\n# ⚠️ Avoid during iterative development\nbundle exec rake test_all\n```\n\n## Documentation\n\n### Source of Truth\n\n**Treat documentation as the source of truth.**\n\nWhen encountering unclear or potentially broken behavior:\n1. Check the documentation first (README.md, inline docs, YARD comments)\n2. If documentation conflicts with implementation, assume documentation is correct\n3. If still unclear, ask for clarification rather than making assumptions\n\nThe documentation defines the intended behavior, and code should be fixed to match it.\n\n=== Operation 2 Result (Text) ===\nWhen executing ruby (eg for tests) or rake tasks, use rvm via the .ruby-version file at the root of the project.\n\n```source ~/.rvm/scripts/rvm && rvm use <ruby_version> && bundle exec <ruby or rake command>```\n\nYou may need to run bundle install if you get gem errors.\n\n```bash -c source ~/.rvm/scripts/rvm && rvm use <ruby_version> && bundle install```"
                  }
                ],
                "status": "Success"
              }
            ]
          }
        },
