    {
      "user": {
        "additional_context": "",
        "env_context": {
          "env_state": {
            "operating_system": "linux",
            "current_working_directory": "/home/ggardner/workspace-ruby/async-mqtt",
            "environment_variables": []
          }
        },
        "content": {
          "Prompt": {
            "prompt": "what is the -u ?"
          }
        },
        "timestamp": "2025-12-03T16:28:40.641581603+01:00",
        "images": null
      },
      "assistant": {
        "Response": {
          "message_id": "0f54a4eb-9f06-4c24-9b41-2a697b26f24b",
          "content": "`-u` is short for `--set-upstream`\n\nIt sets the remote branch as the upstream tracking branch for your local branch. This means:\n\n**With `-u` (first time):**\n```bash\ngit push -u origin ci/release\n```\n- Pushes the branch\n- Sets `origin/ci/release` as the upstream\n- Future pushes can just use `git push` (no need to specify remote/branch)\n\n**Without `-u`:**\n```bash\ngit push origin ci/release\n```\n- Pushes the branch\n- But doesn't set tracking\n- Future pushes need `git push origin ci/release` every time\n\nUse `-u` the first time you push a new branch, then just `git push` after that."
        }
      },
