        "content": {
          "Prompt": {
            "prompt": "OK that's done.  What is our next step to test?"
          }
        },
        "timestamp": "2025-12-03T16:31:03.112058932+01:00",
        "images": null
      },
      "assistant": {
        "Response": {
          "message_id": "770ec12e-714e-447e-b3be-b26bf7fb25ae",
          "content": "Now test the pre-release workflow:\n\n**1. Create pre-release tag:**\n```bash\ncd /home/ggardner/workspace-ruby/async-mqtt\nrake version:tag_prerelease\n```\nThis creates tag `v0.0.1.ci.release`\n\n**2. Push the tag:**\n```bash\ngit push --tags\n```\n\n**3. Check GitHub Actions:**\n- Go to your repo → Actions tab\n- Should see \"Release Gems\" workflow triggered by the tag\n- It will try to build and push gems (will fail without `RUBYGEMS_API_KEY` secret)\n\n**4. Or manually test pre-release check:**\n- Go to Actions → \"Pre-release Check\" \n- Click \"Run workflow\"\n- Branch: `ci/release`\n- Gems: `all`\n- This just builds and shows gem contents (doesn't publish)\n\nWhich do you want to try first? I'd suggest **option 4** (manual pre-release check) since it won't try to publish."
        }
      },
