        "content": {
          "ToolUseResults": {
            "tool_use_results": [
              {
                "tool_use_id": "tooluse_XUEhnnZSQ1O0escRhZJKYA",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "Text": "=== Operation 1 Result (Text) ===\n        ensure\n          io.close\n        end\n\n        def handle_eof\n          client.receive_eof\n          false\n        end\n      end\n    end\n  end\n\n=== Operation 2 Result (Text) ===\n        end\n\n        # Release the pending qos2 packet (return true if we had previously seen it)\n        def qos2_release(id)\n          session_store.qos2_release(id)\n          !!@qos2_pending.delete?(id)\n        end\n\n        # Called when a new subscription arrives.\n        # @return [Array<PUBLISH>] a list of matching packets to enqueue on the subscription.\n        def qos_subscribed(&matcher)\n\n=== Operation 3 Result (Text) ===\n      module BooleanByte\n        module_function\n\n        def read(io)\n          int_value = Int8.read(io)\n          raise ProtocolError, 'Value must be 0 or 1' unless int_value.between?(0, 1)\n\n          !int_value.zero?\n        end\n\n        def write(value, io)\n\n=== Operation 4 Result (Text) ===\n          !!value\n        end\n\n        def default_value\n          false\n        end\n      end\n    end\n\n=== Operation 5 Result (Text) ===\n        # @!visibility private\n        # Explicitly Remove a topic (a previously aliased topic later explicitly set to use alias false)\n        # @param topic [String]\n        def remove(topic)\n          alias_id = @aliases.delete(topic)\n          return false unless alias_id\n\n          @available.push(alias_id)\n          @cached_bytes -= @aliases.delete(alias_id)&.bytesize || 0"
                  }
                ],
                "status": "Success"
              }
            ]
          }
        },
        "timestamp": null,
        "images": null
      },
      "assistant": {
        "Response": {
          "message_id": "47883ba3-8473-441d-b7e3-c69eda839e6b",
          "content": "Ah! Now I see it - **they all return boolean values**:\n\n1. `handle_eof` → returns `false`\n2. `qos2_release(id)` → returns `!!@qos2_pending.delete?(id)` (boolean)\n3. `read(io)` → returns `!int_value.zero?` (boolean)\n4. `default_value` → returns `false`\n5. `remove(topic)` → returns `false` or boolean\n\nThe cop is **correct** - these are predicate methods! They should arguably end with `?`:\n- `handle_eof?`\n- `qos2_release?` or `qos2_released?`\n- `read?` (though this is a standard interface name)\n- `default_value?` (or just return `false` inline)\n- `remove?` or `removed?`\n\nHowever, some are implementing standard interfaces (like `read`) or have semantic meaning beyond just returning boolean. \n\nDo you want to:\n1. Rename them to end with `?`\n2. Disable the cop\n3. Exclude these specific methods"
        }
      },
