        "Response": {
          "message_id": "17c88317-fbcf-483d-8a1b-4514121841c0",
          "content": "That's `gh` CLI authentication, which is separate from git push authentication.\n\nFor git push over HTTPS, you need a credential helper. Try:\n\n```bash\ngit config --global credential.helper store\n```\n\nThen the next time you push, it will prompt for credentials once and store them.\n\nOr use SSH instead:\n```bash\ngit remote set-url origin git@github.com:lwoggardner/ruby-mqtt-gems.git\n```\n\nThen git push will use your SSH key (if you have one set up with GitHub).\n\nWhat does `git remote -v` show?"
        }
      },
