        "Response": {
          "message_id": "4aea0942-b5c9-4399-86f2-b04607e598cd",
          "content": "We were setting up the release infrastructure for your multi-gem MQTT project. Here's where we are:\n\n**Completed:**\n1. ✅ Created release workflows (build.yml, release.yml, pre-release.yml, version-check.yml)\n2. ✅ Set up version management with `GemHelper` \n3. ✅ Fixed version references across all gems (shared `MQTT::VERSION`)\n4. ✅ Fixed Gemfile (removed `optional: true`)\n5. ✅ Updated RuboCop config (plugins syntax)\n6. ✅ Fixed RuboCop offenses\n7. ✅ Pushed to `ci/release` branch\n\n**Next steps to test the release process:**\n1. Check if the GitHub Actions build passed on `ci/release` branch\n2. Test pre-release workflow:\n   - Create pre-release tag: `rake version:tag_prerelease`\n   - Push tag: `git push --tags`\n   - Or manually trigger \"Pre-release Check\" workflow in GitHub Actions\n3. If successful, merge `ci/release` to `main`\n4. Set up `RUBYGEMS_API_KEY` secret for actual releases\n\nWant to check the build status and continue testing?"
        }
      },
