          "content": "It's loading plugin configs but NOT the `.rubocop.yml` from the rubocop-rake gem directory itself. That's good.\n\nBut in CI, maybe RuboCop is running from within vendor/bundle and picking it up? Let me check the CI error path again - it said:\n\n```\nrubocop-rspec extension supports plugin, specify `plugins: rubocop-rspec` instead of `require: rubocop-rspec` in /home/runner/work/ruby-mqtt-gems/ruby-mqtt-gems/vendor/bundle/ruby/3.4.0/gems/rubocop-rake-0.7.1/.rubocop.yml.\n```\n\nSo it IS finding that file in CI. The difference is the `vendor/**/*` exclusion might help, or we need to prevent RuboCop from looking in vendor. Let me try the `inherit_from: ~` approach:",
